<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-11T11:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-11T11:29:00-05:00" n="882" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d882">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 860d.00/–</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-11T19:00:00+02:31"><hi rend="italic">January
                                            11, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received January 13, 8.33
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2217. France formally through Helsingfors Consul recognized
                                independence of Finland. Reported France recognized Ukraine but
                                unable verify. Know France sent a general to Kiev but recognition
                                probably confined thereto. Did France consult us about Finnish
                                recognition?</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_FDR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>